1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,392
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,395 --> 00:00:02,951
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,594 --> 00:00:05,580
(Episode 11)

4
00:00:05,582 --> 00:00:08,230
Did she hit her head or anything?

5
00:00:08,232 --> 00:00:09,854
No, she didn't.

6
00:00:10,449 --> 00:00:14,483
We'll keep an eye on her tonight
and run more tests tomorrow.

7
00:00:14,486 --> 00:00:16,076
I don't need any tests.

8
00:00:16,078 --> 00:00:17,987
My stomach's just upset.

9
00:00:17,990 --> 00:00:19,556
Mom, you're still awake?

10
00:00:19,730 --> 00:00:21,385
How could I sleep?

11
00:00:21,470 --> 00:00:24,988
- I could tear that bastard apart.
- Mom.

12
00:00:26,762 --> 00:00:29,706
Musicians can be quite sensitive.
I'll let her rest.

13
00:00:36,070 --> 00:00:37,182
Seriously!

14
00:00:37,768 --> 00:00:39,863
I keep telling you to watch what you say
because people recognize you,

15
00:00:39,865 --> 00:00:41,521
but you never listen!

16
00:00:42,328 --> 00:00:43,870
Dad spent his whole life...

17
00:00:45,089 --> 00:00:46,559
Your lousy dad!

18
00:00:46,779 --> 00:00:49,374
This is all his fault.

19
00:00:49,376 --> 00:00:51,416
I used to be soft-hearted.

20
00:00:52,757 --> 00:00:56,415
I was so naive that I fell
for his foolish love.

21
00:01:13,346 --> 00:01:14,949
No Yeong Ju.

22
00:01:15,764 --> 00:01:18,103
You need the legal wife's
acknowledgment.

23
00:01:18,105 --> 00:01:22,801
Try getting her to acknowledge
your contribution to his wealth.

24
00:01:31,617 --> 00:01:33,313
You think I'll lose?

25
00:01:34,699 --> 00:01:37,063
My whole life's been a war.

26
00:01:37,410 --> 00:01:39,933
Just let her set foot in this house.

27
00:01:43,387 --> 00:01:45,376
You can't lose.

28
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,957
Just stay put.

29
00:01:47,792 --> 00:01:51,240
Did you hear her? She's just like her mom.

30
00:01:51,243 --> 00:01:52,243
Mai.

31
00:01:52,499 --> 00:01:54,338
I told you I hate that saying.

32
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:56,681
"Like father, like son."
"Like mother, like daughter."

33
00:01:56,926 --> 00:01:57,926
Don't say that.

34
00:01:57,929 --> 00:02:00,291
(Emergency Medical Center)

35
00:02:00,294 --> 00:02:01,895
This is driving me crazy.

36
00:02:02,390 --> 00:02:03,517
What?

37
00:02:03,948 --> 00:02:07,949
- What's driving you crazy?
- You're too mature.

38
00:02:09,175 --> 00:02:12,164
That's not what I mean. You're so rigid.

39
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:14,011
You're like someone
from another generation.

40
00:02:14,013 --> 00:02:15,746
Fine, I'm old-fashioned.

41
00:02:15,748 --> 00:02:17,768
Then meet me halfway.

42
00:02:17,779 --> 00:02:18,926
You're my wife.

43
00:02:24,759 --> 00:02:26,048
How's she feeling?

44
00:02:28,028 --> 00:02:30,248
Why pretend to care
after putting her in the hospital?

45
00:02:32,949 --> 00:02:33,949
Just go.

46
00:02:34,949 --> 00:02:36,353
And the house...

47
00:02:36,439 --> 00:02:38,670
belongs to my mom and my dad,
so give it up.

48
00:02:38,672 --> 00:02:39,805
I can't.

49
00:02:40,220 --> 00:02:42,488
It's our rightful inheritance.

50
00:02:42,490 --> 00:02:45,843
So you're really going to fight this
until the end?

51
00:02:46,570 --> 00:02:49,884
Do you really want to take away
the house where my mom and I live?

52
00:02:49,895 --> 00:02:52,098
Just move somewhere smaller.

53
00:02:52,803 --> 00:02:53,853
Why?

54
00:02:54,316 --> 00:02:57,945
Why should I leave the house
full of my dad's memories?

55
00:02:58,526 --> 00:03:01,723
The law doesn't recognize
a homewrecker's claim to the property.

56
00:03:01,774 --> 00:03:03,643
That's why they register the marriage.

57
00:03:03,645 --> 00:03:05,863
Otherwise, why go through the trouble?

58
00:03:06,818 --> 00:03:08,031
What did you say?

59
00:03:08,749 --> 00:03:10,031
A homewrecker.

60
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:12,849
The law doesn't protect her.

61
00:03:13,734 --> 00:03:16,309
- Stay put.
- If you tell me to stay put again,

62
00:03:16,312 --> 00:03:17,359
I'm going to lose it.

63
00:03:17,361 --> 00:03:18,446
Mai.

64
00:03:18,527 --> 00:03:20,411
The law isn't that foolish.

65
00:03:21,033 --> 00:03:24,411
Don't dismiss everything my mom
contributed to that house...

66
00:03:24,413 --> 00:03:26,950
from the day she signed the contract
until now.

67
00:03:28,431 --> 00:03:30,279
You didn't do anything.

68
00:03:39,513 --> 00:03:41,754
Let's go. O Reum's having a hard time.

69
00:03:49,318 --> 00:03:50,653
I got you admitted.

70
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:54,451
I couldn't reach dad,
so I told Mr. No.

71
00:03:54,910 --> 00:03:57,043
I guess he was having dinner
with Assemblyman Kim.

72
00:03:57,184 --> 00:04:00,111
Then he must've been drinking.
Tell him to go home.

73
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:02,059
I'll be discharged tomorrow anyway.

74
00:04:02,954 --> 00:04:05,414
I just want to sleep for one night
without hearing him snore.

75
00:04:06,388 --> 00:04:08,454
Then, should I stay here tonight?

76
00:04:09,267 --> 00:04:10,267
Yeah.

77
00:04:10,738 --> 00:04:11,738
Okay.

78
00:04:13,330 --> 00:04:16,254
Don't go to the reunion.
You always end up getting sick.

79
00:04:17,187 --> 00:04:19,045
It's all because of your dad.

80
00:04:19,666 --> 00:04:22,236
Other married couples
don't keep secrets from each other,

81
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:25,209
- but your dad never tells me anything.
- Mom.

82
00:04:25,211 --> 00:04:26,553
You don't know.

83
00:04:27,591 --> 00:04:30,173
I feel like I'm
the only one being ignored.

84
00:04:30,175 --> 00:04:31,175
No way.

85
00:04:32,134 --> 00:04:35,048
- Mom, why are women like this?
- What?

86
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:37,288
Is Do Hee like that too?

87
00:04:37,290 --> 00:04:39,745
Do Hee's like a glass princess.

88
00:04:40,029 --> 00:04:41,462
Can't you see everything about her?

89
00:04:42,094 --> 00:04:44,048
I like people like that.

90
00:04:44,078 --> 00:04:46,280
I really hate people I can't figure out.

91
00:04:46,282 --> 00:04:48,108
There are people like that.

92
00:04:48,772 --> 00:04:51,655
What you see and what you sense
can be completely different.

93
00:04:52,899 --> 00:04:55,064
Then what do you trust?

94
00:04:55,066 --> 00:04:56,802
- Who are you talking about?
- Nothing.

95
00:04:56,804 --> 00:04:59,359
I've been meeting
all kinds of people lately.

96
00:05:00,208 --> 00:05:03,253
I don't know. I'm not sure.

97
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:05,869
Go to sleep. The medicine will kick in.

98
00:05:06,177 --> 00:05:08,102
You told your dad not to come, right?

99
00:05:08,218 --> 00:05:09,702
You sleep here tonight.

100
00:05:10,113 --> 00:05:11,371
Okay, I'll stay.

101
00:05:22,843 --> 00:05:26,701
A homewrecker.
The law doesn't protect her.

102
00:05:51,573 --> 00:05:52,867
Hold on to this for me.

103
00:06:12,255 --> 00:06:13,316
Yes, Mr. No.

104
00:06:25,641 --> 00:06:27,929
What? Dad?

105
00:06:29,050 --> 00:06:31,143
But I'm at the hospital right now.

106
00:06:31,835 --> 00:06:33,042
Ji Hu.

107
00:06:33,589 --> 00:06:36,001
- It's me.
- Did you drink a lot?

108
00:06:36,003 --> 00:06:39,545
I did. I don't usually get drunk,

109
00:06:39,618 --> 00:06:42,232
but they kept pressuring me to drink.

110
00:06:42,910 --> 00:06:44,436
Where's your mom?

111
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:46,850
What? Is she sick?

112
00:06:47,008 --> 00:06:48,402
I told you earlier.

113
00:06:48,404 --> 00:06:52,245
- Right, I need to go to the hospital.
- What?

114
00:06:52,882 --> 00:06:55,048
What? She told me not to come?

115
00:06:55,509 --> 00:06:56,960
Because I snore?

116
00:06:58,262 --> 00:07:00,550
I do snore a little.

117
00:07:00,926 --> 00:07:03,183
Your mom doesn't lie.

118
00:07:03,357 --> 00:07:04,751
She doesn't.

119
00:07:05,517 --> 00:07:08,241
I'll sleep here.
You should get some rest too.

120
00:07:08,758 --> 00:07:09,758
Okay.

121
00:07:11,341 --> 00:07:12,441
Ji Hu.

122
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:15,248
I'm not going into politics.

123
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:18,946
I'm not interested in politics.
I'm a sailor.

124
00:07:19,174 --> 00:07:21,026
I'm a soldier.

125
00:07:23,103 --> 00:07:25,453
Now I'm going to publish good books.

126
00:07:25,455 --> 00:07:27,793
Books that make people happy.

127
00:07:28,096 --> 00:07:31,053
- That's who I am.
- I know.

128
00:07:31,408 --> 00:07:34,333
I'll work hard and learn the business
so I can help you.

129
00:07:36,305 --> 00:07:37,352
Dad?

130
00:07:38,202 --> 00:07:39,255
Dad!

131
00:07:51,621 --> 00:07:53,034
I think he's asleep.

132
00:07:55,053 --> 00:07:59,169
Okay. Call me if anything happens
to Mrs. Kim.

133
00:08:31,299 --> 00:08:32,337
You two!

134
00:08:32,629 --> 00:08:34,652
Did you two really go to that house?

135
00:08:38,145 --> 00:08:39,973
Do you think I'm joking?

136
00:08:39,975 --> 00:08:43,858
I made it clear I wasn't moving.
You may want to move,

137
00:08:44,997 --> 00:08:47,558
but I'm against it
if it's because of O Reum's schooling.

138
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:50,740
Anyway, you're his parents.
If you decide to do it and take action,

139
00:08:50,742 --> 00:08:53,000
I said I wouldn't object, right?

140
00:08:53,002 --> 00:08:54,402
Didn't you understand?

141
00:08:55,359 --> 00:08:56,359
What?

142
00:08:57,155 --> 00:08:59,458
- Got it.
- Say it respectfully!

143
00:09:00,093 --> 00:09:02,186
You ranked first at language school,
so why are you talking to me so casually?

144
00:09:02,188 --> 00:09:03,364
Mother.

145
00:09:03,366 --> 00:09:05,840
It's fine for a mother-in-law
and daughter-in-law to be like friends.

146
00:09:05,842 --> 00:09:09,014
It can happen. No, that's a good thing.

147
00:09:09,065 --> 00:09:11,144
But does that mean we're actually friends?

148
00:09:11,206 --> 00:09:13,319
- Can't you tell the difference?
- Mom.

149
00:09:13,321 --> 00:09:16,458
Are you stupid? Why do you let her
push you around? You know I hate this.

150
00:09:16,682 --> 00:09:20,598
How could you say
you have rights to that house?

151
00:09:20,749 --> 00:09:22,741
People should have a conscience.

152
00:09:23,110 --> 00:09:24,750
That's someone else's house!

153
00:09:29,465 --> 00:09:32,371
- Mai.
- Back in my day, you'd get a beating!

154
00:09:32,373 --> 00:09:33,646
Seung Hyun, Seung Woo.

155
00:09:34,119 --> 00:09:36,352
I even smacked their calves
after they finished military service.

156
00:09:36,731 --> 00:09:40,135
- You hit them?
- Did you pretend to cry?

157
00:09:46,244 --> 00:09:48,343
That's why you always get fooled.

158
00:09:48,845 --> 00:09:50,196
We'll move out ourselves.

159
00:09:50,729 --> 00:09:52,152
We'll move into my dad's apartment.

160
00:09:53,573 --> 00:09:56,840
- We'll talk about it later.
- Go. Why talk about it later?

161
00:09:56,890 --> 00:09:58,460
You're her husband.

162
00:09:59,325 --> 00:10:01,158
Focus on being her husband.
You don't have to take care of me.

163
00:10:01,581 --> 00:10:04,547
- I still have another son. Don't worry.
- Mother.

164
00:10:04,549 --> 00:10:05,741
That's not right.

165
00:10:05,743 --> 00:10:07,047
It's my decision.

166
00:10:17,924 --> 00:10:20,479
- Are you awake, O Reum?
- Grandma.

167
00:10:23,472 --> 00:10:26,386
Seung Hyun, bring O Reum's cough syrup.

168
00:10:26,536 --> 00:10:27,640
Okay.

169
00:10:28,996 --> 00:10:31,492
Why won't this summer cold go away?

170
00:10:32,252 --> 00:10:34,428
I feel so bad for you.

171
00:10:35,732 --> 00:10:38,404
- Are you angry, Grandma?
- No.

172
00:10:38,452 --> 00:10:41,341
You shouted at mom.

173
00:10:42,692 --> 00:10:44,140
No, I didn't.

174
00:10:44,999 --> 00:10:46,628
You don't like it when I scold your mom?

175
00:10:48,076 --> 00:10:50,210
My little sweetheart.

176
00:10:52,968 --> 00:10:55,024
Come here. Let me check. That's it.

177
00:10:55,092 --> 00:10:56,440
- Mom.
- Yes.

178
00:10:57,068 --> 00:10:58,739
O Reum, time for your cough syrup.

179
00:11:00,156 --> 00:11:01,760
Good.

180
00:11:06,324 --> 00:11:08,747
What about the hit-and-run biker
I asked you to track down?

181
00:11:08,756 --> 00:11:09,823
Another dead end?

182
00:11:12,496 --> 00:11:14,298
I can't leave this neighborhood...

183
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,165
until I catch that guy.

184
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:20,164
Your grandfather's final wish was...

185
00:11:20,996 --> 00:11:24,482
to catch whoever did that to Seung Woo
and make him pay.

186
00:11:27,550 --> 00:11:28,980
Do what feels right to you.

187
00:11:30,041 --> 00:11:32,373
Mai has a point too.

188
00:11:32,672 --> 00:11:34,268
I'm here too.

189
00:11:34,450 --> 00:11:35,650
I can't leave you, Mom.

190
00:11:36,127 --> 00:11:37,932
It's okay. You should go.

191
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:41,073
If I can let my husband go,
I can let my son go too.

192
00:11:52,270 --> 00:11:55,639
- Thank you.
- You're staying with this guy longer.

193
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:58,771
- What?
- Break up before you get attached.

194
00:11:58,928 --> 00:12:00,593
Breaking up before we get too close...

195
00:12:00,968 --> 00:12:01,976
is our unspoken rule, right?

196
00:12:02,016 --> 00:12:05,066
Don't compare him to the losers you date.

197
00:12:05,770 --> 00:12:07,853
What, you love him? That guy with no legs?

198
00:12:07,856 --> 00:12:10,514
- Watch your mouth.
- Watch who you date.

199
00:12:10,570 --> 00:12:12,306
Think about my dignity too.

200
00:12:13,204 --> 00:12:15,002
Am I really supposed to lose
to a guy like him?

201
00:12:16,414 --> 00:12:17,464
Han Jeong Won.

202
00:12:18,076 --> 00:12:19,835
Know your place
while I'm still being nice.

203
00:12:19,837 --> 00:12:21,341
Thanks for the ride.

204
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:33,053
- Ms. Han!
- Hey.

205
00:12:36,684 --> 00:12:39,856
- Did you have lunch?
- Want to eat together later?

206
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:48,530
It's me.

207
00:12:49,424 --> 00:12:51,453
Let's teach some bastard a lesson.

208
00:12:59,348 --> 00:13:00,508
Who was that?

209
00:13:01,777 --> 00:13:04,158
- My brother.
- You should've introduced us.

210
00:13:04,286 --> 00:13:06,274
Later. Let's go.

211
00:13:19,856 --> 00:13:22,081
Jeon Jung A, when did you get so pretty?

212
00:13:23,890 --> 00:13:26,841
Do Do Hee, mean as ever. What do you want?

213
00:13:26,844 --> 00:13:28,597
Why are you so defensive?

214
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,614
How's the new artists' exhibition going?

215
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:32,645
Focus on your own exhibition.

216
00:13:32,648 --> 00:13:35,258
I just want to see you
hold an exhibition before I die.

217
00:13:35,644 --> 00:13:37,645
- You're not painting, are you?
- I am.

218
00:13:37,648 --> 00:13:39,802
I may not be a genius,
but I can tell the difference...

219
00:13:39,804 --> 00:13:41,349
between someone who paints
and someone who doesn't.

220
00:13:41,352 --> 00:13:43,027
I told you I'm painting.

221
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,613
I'm going to have an exhibition.

222
00:13:45,130 --> 00:13:46,804
You lied about the school bullying, right?

223
00:13:46,806 --> 00:13:48,537
You scared me.

224
00:13:49,652 --> 00:13:50,830
What bullying?

225
00:13:50,888 --> 00:13:53,124
You lied about being bullied, right?

226
00:13:53,170 --> 00:13:54,448
That's a false accusation.

227
00:13:54,536 --> 00:13:56,741
Since when do art students
throw around legal terms?

228
00:13:56,744 --> 00:13:58,404
- You're lying.
- No, I'm not.

229
00:13:58,451 --> 00:14:01,087
I don't know how you managed
to cover the whole thing up,

230
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:03,148
but nothing stays hidden.
I'll find out the truth.

231
00:14:03,231 --> 00:14:05,190
You? Why?

232
00:14:05,252 --> 00:14:07,072
Because my friend was wronged.

233
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:10,147
Because your lie cost her
her place in the competition.

234
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:12,182
Just you wait.

235
00:14:12,452 --> 00:14:14,116
Karma is coming for you.

236
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:20,210
Crazy bitch. What a performance.

237
00:14:24,761 --> 00:14:26,830
How did you hear about the vacancy?

238
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,907
The girl who left to study abroad
was my classmate in arts high school.

239
00:14:28,990 --> 00:14:30,525
It's a small world around here.

240
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:32,638
Could you ask Ji Ni to take that spot?

241
00:14:32,944 --> 00:14:34,525
You said her paintings were good.

242
00:14:34,784 --> 00:14:37,143
Yes, they are.

243
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:40,968
They're sad but resilient,
and hopeful without feeling superficial.

244
00:14:42,651 --> 00:14:44,797
The figures' expressions feel unique.

245
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,600
But...

246
00:14:47,508 --> 00:14:49,454
I guess you understand
why it was rejected.

247
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:52,538
- That's not true.
- Do you have proof?

248
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:55,664
Do you have proof
that Ji Ni bullied someone?

249
00:14:55,688 --> 00:14:57,045
I saw it myself.

250
00:14:58,952 --> 00:15:01,209
I wouldn't have believed it either
if I hadn't seen it.

251
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:03,693
Tae O, you,

252
00:15:04,764 --> 00:15:06,733
and even Professor Bae
all say it isn't true.

253
00:15:06,970 --> 00:15:10,155
Most of all, her paintings
tell me she isn't like that.

254
00:15:10,192 --> 00:15:11,518
I'm confused too.

255
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,707
No, that's impossible.

256
00:15:14,710 --> 00:15:16,004
There's no way Ji Ni would do that.

257
00:15:16,048 --> 00:15:19,924
It's nice to see you
stand up for your friend.

258
00:15:19,948 --> 00:15:23,200
But you shouldn't act on suspicion
without clear evidence.

259
00:15:23,530 --> 00:15:25,258
Please focus on your work.

260
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,620
I'll go now.

261
00:15:33,428 --> 00:15:35,421
- He saw it?
- Yeah.

262
00:15:35,436 --> 00:15:38,296
He says he saw you bullying Do Hee.
Does that make sense?

263
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:42,025
He did see something.

264
00:15:42,028 --> 00:15:43,382
Really?

265
00:15:43,508 --> 00:15:44,925
When, where, why?

266
00:15:45,512 --> 00:15:49,636
I decided not to hold back
and was about to kick Do Do Hee.

267
00:15:49,668 --> 00:15:51,204
That's when he saw me.

268
00:15:52,140 --> 00:15:55,657
Thinking about it now,
Do Do Hee probably set me up.

269
00:15:55,810 --> 00:15:58,524
She must've seen him behind me.

270
00:16:00,168 --> 00:16:03,307
So when he came up behind you,
she suddenly dropped to the ground?

271
00:16:03,310 --> 00:16:04,877
To make it look like you'd kicked her?

272
00:16:05,780 --> 00:16:07,791
- That must've looked undeniable.
- Yeah.

273
00:16:08,290 --> 00:16:09,849
That's why I couldn't defend myself.

274
00:16:10,932 --> 00:16:13,292
Still, if he's smart,

275
00:16:13,328 --> 00:16:15,544
shouldn't he have asked
what really happened?

276
00:16:15,616 --> 00:16:18,162
But he just decided
you were the aggressor.

277
00:16:19,060 --> 00:16:20,304
Forget it.

278
00:16:21,568 --> 00:16:23,637
I have other things I want to draw anyway.

279
00:16:24,868 --> 00:16:25,979
I'm over it.

280
00:16:26,731 --> 00:16:27,731
Animation?

281
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:30,425
- Yeah.
- You're going to get a job?

282
00:16:31,664 --> 00:16:32,952
I'm looking into it.

283
00:16:34,196 --> 00:16:38,109
Right. Your father supported
your decision to pursue animation.

284
00:16:38,111 --> 00:16:39,196
That makes sense.

285
00:16:39,504 --> 00:16:41,856
But at least that guy has a good eye.

286
00:16:42,392 --> 00:16:45,393
He says the people you draw
look sad, but strong.

287
00:16:45,912 --> 00:16:48,707
- Really?
- Yeah. Funny, right?

288
00:17:11,664 --> 00:17:12,794
Ji Ni.

289
00:17:13,224 --> 00:17:14,294
Ji Ni?

290
00:17:16,384 --> 00:17:17,648
Ji Ni, it's your dad.

291
00:17:20,890 --> 00:17:22,108
Ji Ni.

292
00:17:39,376 --> 00:17:40,669
Ji Ni, it's okay.

293
00:17:41,768 --> 00:17:43,564
It's okay. None of that matters.

294
00:17:43,690 --> 00:17:45,505
As long as you're safe and alive,

295
00:17:46,224 --> 00:17:47,610
that's all I care about.

296
00:17:48,398 --> 00:17:50,038
So please, my dear,

297
00:17:50,996 --> 00:17:52,554
don't ever do this again, okay?

298
00:18:11,872 --> 00:18:14,948
Want to go out together?
Let's go to a Van Gogh exhibition.

299
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:21,264
Let's go.

300
00:18:21,504 --> 00:18:24,243
When you look at paintings,
you come back to life.

301
00:18:24,970 --> 00:18:26,947
You said painting is how you breathe.

302
00:18:45,895 --> 00:18:48,942
("Almond Blossom")

303
00:18:59,736 --> 00:19:01,718
It's okay if you don't go to high school.

304
00:19:02,096 --> 00:19:03,608
I will wait.

305
00:19:04,270 --> 00:19:06,392
It's okay if this is as far
as you go in school.

306
00:19:06,430 --> 00:19:07,544
But...

307
00:19:08,316 --> 00:19:10,957
don't give up the art
that keeps you alive.

308
00:19:11,504 --> 00:19:15,348
The love, warmth, and comfort
in your paintings...

309
00:19:15,980 --> 00:19:17,715
I saw all of that.

310
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:21,184
Can you see comfort in them?

311
00:19:21,228 --> 00:19:23,350
Of course. I'm a director.

312
00:19:23,396 --> 00:19:24,752
I've got a good eye.

313
00:19:24,910 --> 00:19:27,287
The expressions of the people
in your drawings,

314
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:31,856
even when they smile,
they carry a depth that's uniquely yours.

315
00:19:33,430 --> 00:19:36,009
Others may earn diplomas at school,

316
00:19:37,192 --> 00:19:41,290
but you can build your own world
through your art.

317
00:19:42,310 --> 00:19:44,080
You don't need a diploma.

318
00:19:44,770 --> 00:19:46,772
Your mom and I will support you.

319
00:19:51,238 --> 00:19:54,042
Let me learn a sport too. Kickboxing.

320
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:57,652
- Kickboxing?
- I want to protect myself.

321
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:00,900
Instead of always relying on you,

322
00:20:01,868 --> 00:20:03,235
I want to protect myself.

323
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:28,182
Mom, are you okay? Get some rest.

324
00:20:28,206 --> 00:20:31,546
- Do you have a concert?
- No. I got fired.

325
00:20:32,606 --> 00:20:33,815
Really?

326
00:20:34,565 --> 00:20:36,731
Don't worry. I won't let you starve.

327
00:20:37,257 --> 00:20:39,437
But I can't just stop practicing.

328
00:20:39,825 --> 00:20:41,418
Even one day of practice matters.

329
00:20:42,190 --> 00:20:43,604
You should draw more too.

330
00:20:43,606 --> 00:20:45,215
Keep improving and prove them wrong.

331
00:20:46,731 --> 00:20:48,894
Mom, I'll get a job.

332
00:20:49,773 --> 00:20:50,773
What?

333
00:20:51,565 --> 00:20:54,478
- If we give her half of this house...
- Give? Give it to whom?

334
00:20:54,481 --> 00:20:56,016
That will never happen.

335
00:20:56,481 --> 00:20:58,020
I looked into it too.

336
00:20:58,023 --> 00:20:59,355
That woman...

337
00:20:59,856 --> 00:21:02,328
I know. Don't say it.

338
00:21:03,356 --> 00:21:05,271
I'd die before I give up this house.

339
00:21:05,273 --> 00:21:06,856
I'll live here to the very end,

340
00:21:06,898 --> 00:21:08,271
then leave it to you when I die,

341
00:21:08,273 --> 00:21:09,521
so don't say anything else.

342
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:13,398
I paid the down payment,
and I'm paying off the loan.

343
00:21:13,481 --> 00:21:15,971
- Mom.
- Don't talk nonsense about getting a job.

344
00:21:16,415 --> 00:21:18,260
You only know how to draw.

345
00:21:18,273 --> 00:21:19,438
What kind of job would you get?

346
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:21,026
I'm not a little kid.

347
00:21:21,978 --> 00:21:23,478
You're not alone, Mom.

348
00:21:23,481 --> 00:21:24,690
I'm here too.

349
00:21:31,586 --> 00:21:33,231
There are two of us.

350
00:21:33,356 --> 00:21:34,876
Don't worry, Mom.

351
00:21:40,773 --> 00:21:42,095
Let's make dinner.

352
00:21:42,315 --> 00:21:43,784
I'll make you something delicious.

353
00:21:45,273 --> 00:21:46,651
You can't cook.

354
00:21:47,190 --> 00:21:48,398
Dad...

355
00:21:54,731 --> 00:21:56,713
I'll try doing it the way your dad did.

356
00:21:57,565 --> 00:21:58,773
Okay.

357
00:21:58,940 --> 00:22:00,446
I'll wash my hands.
Let's make it together.

358
00:22:12,106 --> 00:22:14,515
I hate you so much.

359
00:22:15,481 --> 00:22:16,858
Just wait.

360
00:22:17,231 --> 00:22:19,769
Once Ji Ni is married,
I'll come for you...

361
00:22:24,898 --> 00:22:27,815
So, did you manage to eat anything?

362
00:22:27,856 --> 00:22:30,690
How could I? It was a total disaster.

363
00:22:30,946 --> 00:22:32,964
We threw it all out and ordered in.

364
00:22:35,231 --> 00:22:38,978
My daughter said she'd get a job,

365
00:22:38,981 --> 00:22:42,090
and I just wanted to hug her and cry.

366
00:22:49,425 --> 00:22:51,458
Stay strong. You still have your daughter.

367
00:22:54,856 --> 00:22:57,576
His legal wife's son
and daughter-in-law came to see the house.

368
00:22:59,315 --> 00:23:02,119
Goodness, they're heartless.

369
00:23:02,556 --> 00:23:05,478
As if holding on to the papers
for 25 years wasn't enough,

370
00:23:05,481 --> 00:23:07,148
now they want to take the house?

371
00:23:08,336 --> 00:23:10,436
Wasn't this her plan all along?

372
00:23:10,856 --> 00:23:12,343
Of course it was.

373
00:23:12,523 --> 00:23:14,311
I was the only fool who didn't know.

374
00:23:14,481 --> 00:23:16,940
She must've known everything
and held out until now.

375
00:23:17,815 --> 00:23:21,262
I really lived like a fool.

376
00:23:22,562 --> 00:23:24,395
That legal wife of his...

377
00:23:24,398 --> 00:23:25,606
She's really scary.

378
00:23:27,023 --> 00:23:29,569
I'm really glad you're by my side, Sa Bin.

379
00:23:30,815 --> 00:23:32,940
I can't let my daughter see me like this.

380
00:23:33,481 --> 00:23:34,690
Right.

381
00:23:35,725 --> 00:23:37,892
Call me anytime.
Don't keep it all to yourself.

382
00:23:39,231 --> 00:23:40,637
Let's stop talking now.

383
00:23:40,773 --> 00:23:42,103
Try to eat a little.

384
00:23:45,273 --> 00:23:47,515
Okay. Thank you.

385
00:23:54,315 --> 00:23:55,523
Knock, knock.

386
00:23:56,859 --> 00:23:58,025
Mrs. No, this is for you.

387
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,690
What's all this?

388
00:23:59,731 --> 00:24:01,604
A woman I care about
recently lost her husband,

389
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:03,604
so I took her to lunch to comfort her.

390
00:24:03,606 --> 00:24:05,981
I thought of you,
so I packed this separately.

391
00:24:06,145 --> 00:24:07,728
I put in plenty,

392
00:24:07,881 --> 00:24:09,422
so have it for dinner with your family.

393
00:24:09,690 --> 00:24:11,606
Is it really okay for me to accept this?

394
00:24:11,648 --> 00:24:14,856
Can't a student give something like this
to their teacher?

395
00:24:14,898 --> 00:24:16,898
It feels a bit strange
to call yourself my student.

396
00:24:18,212 --> 00:24:19,267
Mrs. No.

397
00:24:19,613 --> 00:24:21,563
I heard even tone-deafness
can be corrected.

398
00:24:21,566 --> 00:24:23,232
Do you think someone like me could do it?

399
00:24:23,284 --> 00:24:24,830
Tone-deaf treatment?

400
00:24:25,481 --> 00:24:26,938
Yes, it's possible.

401
00:24:26,940 --> 00:24:27,940
Really?

402
00:24:28,416 --> 00:24:29,779
Then I want to try.

403
00:24:30,523 --> 00:24:32,555
You must really like singing.

404
00:24:33,398 --> 00:24:35,521
My late mother loved it.

405
00:24:35,523 --> 00:24:36,938
But now that I think about it,

406
00:24:36,940 --> 00:24:39,354
she was probably tone-deaf.

407
00:24:39,356 --> 00:24:40,606
My brother and I...

408
00:24:40,648 --> 00:24:43,148
grew up thinking that was
how singing was supposed to sound.

409
00:24:43,940 --> 00:24:45,218
That can happen.

410
00:24:45,273 --> 00:24:48,356
Then shall we work on it together?

411
00:24:50,231 --> 00:24:51,440
Thank you.

412
00:24:53,398 --> 00:24:55,377
Thank you too.

413
00:24:56,106 --> 00:24:57,106
Okay.

414
00:25:02,180 --> 00:25:03,285
Ji Ni, coffee.

415
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:06,717
Table one.

416
00:25:15,486 --> 00:25:16,694
Thank you.

417
00:25:24,106 --> 00:25:26,898
You work here?

418
00:25:28,776 --> 00:25:30,009
Wait.

419
00:25:30,356 --> 00:25:32,356
There's something
I really need to tell you.

420
00:25:33,481 --> 00:25:35,629
Let go. I said, let go!

421
00:25:41,190 --> 00:25:42,816
The woman you're dating...

422
00:25:44,231 --> 00:25:45,440
She's married.

423
00:25:45,481 --> 00:25:46,848
Break up with her.

424
00:25:47,940 --> 00:25:49,106
What...

425
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:52,237
Just because I spoke to you
at the funeral,

426
00:25:52,690 --> 00:25:54,837
you think we're on speaking terms?

427
00:25:55,481 --> 00:25:57,226
Stop talking nonsense and get lost.

428
00:25:57,690 --> 00:26:00,325
I guess I can't come here anymore.

429
00:26:17,356 --> 00:26:19,478
Jeong Won, we should move somewhere else.

430
00:26:19,481 --> 00:26:20,690
Don't come here.

431
00:26:27,773 --> 00:26:29,358
So it's true.

432
00:26:37,211 --> 00:26:38,229
What's with you guys?

433
00:26:38,231 --> 00:26:40,450
We're here to teach punks
like you a lesson...

434
00:26:40,523 --> 00:26:42,656
for messing with a married woman.

435
00:26:43,606 --> 00:26:44,815
A married woman?

436
00:27:03,964 --> 00:27:05,652
Are you crazy?

437
00:27:14,815 --> 00:27:16,446
Hey, you jerks!

438
00:27:18,356 --> 00:27:19,534
What is this?

439
00:27:21,398 --> 00:27:23,273
- This is ridiculous.
- Hey, come here.

440
00:27:24,815 --> 00:27:26,148
What on earth...

441
00:27:35,731 --> 00:27:37,646
What are you doing, you bastards?

442
00:27:37,648 --> 00:27:40,062
Hey, stop!

443
00:27:40,065 --> 00:27:41,148
Run!

444
00:28:16,731 --> 00:28:20,021
(Family Register)

445
00:28:20,023 --> 00:28:22,106
If I really wanted to,
I could take everything from you.

446
00:28:22,148 --> 00:28:23,354
Yeong Ju, please.

447
00:28:23,356 --> 00:28:24,898
Should I even get on my knees and beg?

448
00:28:24,940 --> 00:28:26,273
Were you really kicked out?

449
00:28:26,315 --> 00:28:27,815
Why? Does that bother you now?

450
00:28:27,856 --> 00:28:31,188
Fun, money, desire, necessity...
love is no different from any of them.

451
00:28:31,190 --> 00:28:32,938
I think people who believe
love is special...

452
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:34,188
are all naive.

453
00:28:34,190 --> 00:28:35,819
It's not an affair.
This is different from what my dad did.

454
00:28:35,822 --> 00:28:37,771
What's different? Do you think...

455
00:28:37,773 --> 00:28:39,096
you can avoid being called just like him?

456
00:28:41,929 --> 00:28:43,929
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
